STAY SAFE ONLINE – CYBERBULLYING PREVENTION

1. When you see mean messages or people being nasty online just ignore them. Do not write back to these people.

2. If someone is being very mean to you block that person away. You should also tell the website or app people about what happened.

3. Make sure your social media accounts are locked so only your friends can see what you post. This is a way to stay safe online.

4. Be careful what you share online. Do not tell people your secrets or things that're private. Remember the internet is a place.

5. Before you post something or write a comment think about it for a moment. Ask yourself if it is an idea to share this with everyone.

6. If you see someone being bullied online try to help them or support them. Cyberbullying is not okay. We should all help each other stay safe online.

7. If someone is bullying you online take a picture of the screen so you have proof of what happened. This can be very helpful later.

8. If you feel scared or uncomfortable talk to someone you trust like a parent or a teacher. They can help you deal with the situation and stay online.

